matched.actualTitle: MD5 Hash Type Juggling Authentication Bypass via Magic Hash Collision
matched.matchReason: Both findings describe identical vulnerability: PHP loose comparison (==) of MD5 hashes allowing authentication bypass. The actual finding provides detailed proof of concept showing magic hash collision at 0e662097431906509019562988736854 == 0e678703625362188185747119782643 with payload 240610708 bypassing admin authentication. Both address CWE-1025 and CWE-327 with same attack scenario and impact.

extra.title: Directory Listing Enabled on /static/ Endpoint
extra.assessment: New discovery - not in expected findings. Legitimate vulnerability where Python SimpleHTTPRequestHandler defaults to directory listing enabled, exposing file structure and enabling enumeration of static assets without authentication. Verified to return HTTP 200 with directory listing.

extra.title: Path Traversal Vulnerability in /static/ Directory
extra.assessment: New discovery - not in expected findings. Legitimate vulnerability where path traversal sequences (../) are not validated, allowing escape from /static/ directory. Confirmed to allow access to parent directories and root directory listing through path normalization bypass.

extra.title: Server Information Disclosure via HTTP Headers
extra.assessment: New discovery - not in expected findings. Legitimate information disclosure where Server header reveals 'SimpleHTTP/0.6 Python/3.13.3', exposing technology stack and version information that aids attacker reconnaissance.
